: 2736, \"to\": 2757}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thanks to their enthusiasm for leading in such a major event, the gap for the half dozen ahead reached well over six minutes.\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their enthusiasm\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2792}, {\"ngram\": \"such a major event\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2826}, {\"ngram\": \"the gap\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2835}, {\"ngram\": \"the half dozen\", \"from\": 2840, \"to\": 2854}, {\"ngram\": \"well over six minutes\", \"from\": 2869, \"to\": 2890}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This in turn forced favourites Belgium and then Netherlands, one of a handful of teams with four riders, to defend the peloton's interests, with veteran Ellen van Dijk doing much of the spadework in her last-ever Games.\", \"from\": 2892, \"to\": 3111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2923, \"end\": 2930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7680242936222178, \"rank\": 0.3020421467191595, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2940, \"end\": 2951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8580871174604618, \"rank\": 0.16538283736432693, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3045, \"end\": 3059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellen_van_Dijk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ellen van Dijk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellen_van_Dijk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ellen_van_Dijk\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"turn\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2904}, {\"ngram\": \"favourites\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"a handful\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 2969}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 2973, \"to\": 2978}, {\"ngram\": \"four riders\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 2995}, {\"ngram\": \"the peloton's interests\", \"from\": 3007, \"to\": 3030}, {\"ngram\": \"the spadework\", \"from\": 3074, \"to\": 3087}, {\"ngram\": \"her last-ever Games\", \"from\": 3091, \"to\": 3110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The subsequent rise in pace left defending Olympic champion Anna Kiesenhofer (Austria), already on the back foot after several bad crashes in the time trial a week earlier, struggling slightly.\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3306, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3173, \"end\": 3189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Kiesenhofer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Kiesenhofer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Kiesenhofer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Kiesenhofer\"}, {\"begin\": 3191, \"end\": 3198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"score\": 0.9999999984702299, \"rank\": 1.4704840521281011e-09, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The subsequent rise\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3132}, {\"ngram\": \"pace\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3140}, {\"ngram\": \"the back foot\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3225}, {\"ngram\": \"several bad crashes\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3251}, {\"ngram\": \"the time trial\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it did not prevent another chaser, Olga Zabelinskaya (Uzbekistan) making a courageous but ultimately futile solo effort to bridge across to the six.\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3346, \"end\": 3363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olga_Zabelinskaya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olga Zabelinskaya\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olga_Zabelinskaya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olga_Zabelinskaya\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another chaser\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3344}, {\"ngram\": \"Uzbekistan\", \"from\": 3365, \"to\": 3375}, {\"ngram\": \"a courageous but ultimately futile solo effort\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3430}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The working alliance in the six-rider early break was so effective that they not only waited for Jencusova when her chain dropped, they even tried to help her reship it.\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3630, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The working alliance\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3481}, {\"ngram\": \"the six-rider early break\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3510}, {\"ngram\": \"Jencusova\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3567}, {\"ngram\": \"her chain\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3582}, {\"ngram\": \"her reship\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3626}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But while they managed to do so, it was clear the half dozen race leaders could not hang around, as Van Dijk made the most of her time trialling prowess to blast past counter attacker Zabelinskaya and shred the break's lead to just two minutes in the process.\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"race leaders\", \"from\": 3693, \"to\": 3705}, {\"ngram\": \"Van Dijk\", \"from\": 3732, \"to\": 3740}, {\"ngram\": \"her time\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3766}, {\"ngram\": \"prowess\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 3784}, {\"ngram\": \"past counter attacker Zabelinskaya\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3828}, {\"ngram\": \"the break's lead\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3855}, {\"ngram\": \"just two minutes\", \"from\": 3859, \"to\": 3875}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 3879, \"to\": 3890}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For all Van Dijk's work was impressive, as the kilometres clicked down the bunch was growing increasingly restless behind her, finally seeing veteran Mavi Garc\\u00eda (Spain) make the first serious move by one of the top contenders.\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 4120, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4043, \"end\": 4054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Victoria_Garc\\u00eda\", \"score\": 0.9999999439651235, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mavi Garc\\u00eda\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Victoria_Garc\\u00eda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Victoria_Garc\\u00eda\"}, {\"begin\": 4056, \"end\": 4061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9876232812877979, \"rank\": 0.012531688355086484, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all Van Dijk's work\", \"from\": 3897, \"to\": 3916}, {\"ngram\": \"the kilometres\", \"from\": 3936, \"to\": 3950}, {\"ngram\": \"the bunch\", \"from\": 3964, \"to\": 3973}, {\"ngram\": \"the first serious move\", \"from\": 4068, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"the top contenders\", \"from\": 4101, \"to\": 4119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably sharper digs by Olympic silver TT medallist Anna Henderson and Great Britain teammate Elizabeth Deignan then caused another couple of sizable rents in the size of the pack and a lengthy period of probing attacks quickly developed, shredding the peloton to perhaps 40 riders at most.\", \"from\": 4122, \"to\": 4412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4161, \"end\": 4163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man\", \"score\": 0.625655057514805, \"rank\": 0.5983248085062765, \"text\": \"TT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man\"}, {\"begin\": 4174, \"end\": 4188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"score\": 0.9999958972005097, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\"}, {\"begin\": 4193, \"end\": 4206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9949418724559201, \"rank\": 0.005083810857900807, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 4216, \"end\": 4225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.8574492964342019, \"rank\": 0.16620671730227718, \"text\": \"Elizabeth\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\"}, {\"begin\": 4226, \"end\": 4233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deignan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Notably sharper digs\", \"from\": 4122, \"to\": 4142}, {\"ngram\": \"another couple\", \"from\": 4246, \"to\": 4260}, {\"ngram\": \"sizable rents\", \"from\": 4264, \"to\": 4277}, {\"ngram\": \"the size\", \"from\": 4281, \"to\": 4289}, {\"ngram\": \"the pack\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4301}, {\"ngram\": \"a lengthy period\", \"from\": 4306, \"to\": 4322}, {\"ngram\": \"probing attacks\", \"from\": 4326, \"to\": 4341}, {\"ngram\": \"the peloton\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4382}, {\"ngram\": \"perhaps 40 riders\", \"from\": 4386, \"to\": 4403}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back in the suburbs of Paris, Henderson made one dangerous move, but it was when 2012 gold medallist Vos briefly counter-attacked that the alarm bells truly went off in the much-reduced pack.\", \"from\": 4414, \"to\": 4605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4437, \"end\": 4442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5151722039303781e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 4444, \"end\": 4453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999995225153, \"rank\": 2.336888229451519e-10, \"text\": \"Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the suburbs\", \"from\": 4422, \"to\": 4433}, {\"ngram\": \"one dangerous move\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4477}, {\"ngram\": \"2012 gold medallist Vos\", \"from\": 4495, \"to\": 4518}, {\"ngram\": \"the alarm bells\", \"from\": 4549, \"to\": 4564}, {\"ngram\": \"the much-reduced pack\", \"from\": 4583, \"to\": 4604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The break's advantage was tumbling fast now, and the Netherlands continued to chase down challenges as best they could, snuffing out a probe by former Paris-Roubaix winner Alison Jackson (Canada) and another by Megan Armitage (Ireland).\", \"from\": 4607, \"to\": 4843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4660, \"end\": 4671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8580871174604618, \"rank\": 0.16538283736432693, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4758, \"end\": 4771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"score\": 0.9816675037644488, \"rank\": 0.004431782209560121, \"text\": \"Paris-Roubaix\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\"}, {\"begin\": 4779, \"end\": 4793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_Jackson_(artist)\", \"score\": 0.7719295423990269, \"rank\": 0.29545454545454364, \"text\": \"Alison Jackson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_Jackson_(artist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alison_Jackson_(artist)\"}, {\"begin\": 4795, \"end\": 4801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9984634379382102, \"rank\": 0.001538917762470239, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 4818, \"end\": 4823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\", \"score\": 0.9999999346864591, \"rank\": 6.531341742618181e-08, \"text\": \"Megan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\"}, {\"begin\": 4824, \"end\": 4832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armitage\", \"score\": 0.9999998903813381, \"rank\": 1.0928669401501374e-07, \"text\": \"Armitage\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armitage\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armitage\"}, {\"begin\": 4834, \"end\": 4841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9996103833057148, \"rank\": 0.0002853797757556799, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The break's advantage\", \"from\": 4607, \"to\": 4628}, {\"ngram\": \"challenges\", \"from\": 4696, \"to\": 4706}, {\"ngram\": \"a probe\", \"from\": 4740, \"to\": 4747}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 4807, \"to\": 4814}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vos remained the key guardian for the Netherlands at this point as the race roared alongside the River Seine.\", \"from\": 4844, \"to\": 4953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4882, \"end\": 4893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8580871174604618, \"rank\": 0.16538283736432693, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4941, \"end\": 4952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 4844, \"to\": 4847}, {\"ngram\": \"the key guardian\", \"from\": 4857, \"to\": 4873}, {\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 4897, \"to\": 4907}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 4911, \"to\": 4919}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then as the Butte Montmartre ascent approached and the last two survivors of the break, Fariba Hashimi (Afghanistan) and Hannah Tserakh (Neutral), all but threw in the towel, it was clear the race was reaching a pivotal moment.\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 5181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4972, \"end\": 4982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7408908238508796e-16, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}, {\"begin\": 5042, \"end\": 5048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Behtash_Fariba\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fariba\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Behtash_Fariba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Behtash_Fariba\"}, {\"begin\": 5058, \"end\": 5069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6634168889476807e-13, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last two survivors\", \"from\": 5005, \"to\": 5027}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 5031, \"to\": 5040}, {\"ngram\": \"Hannah Tserakh\", \"from\": 5075, \"to\": 5089}, {\"ngram\": \"Neutral\", \"from\": 5091, \"to\": 5098}, {\"ngram\": \"the towel\", \"from\": 5118, \"to\": 5127}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 5142, \"to\": 5150}, {\"ngram\": \"a pivotal moment\", \"from\": 5164, \"to\": 5180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather than an attack, though, initially it was a bad crash on the right side of the narrow, cobbled, road at the bottom of the Montmartre that really threw the race cards up in the air.\", \"from\": 5183, \"to\": 5369, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an attack\", \"from\": 5195, \"to\": 5204}, {\"ngram\": \"a bad crash\", \"from\": 5231, \"to\": 5242}, {\"ngram\": \"the right side\", \"from\": 5246, \"to\": 5260}, {\"ngram\": \"the narrow, cobbled, road\", \"from\": 5264, \"to\": 5289}, {\"ngram\": \"the bottom\", \"from\": 5293, \"to\": 5303}, {\"ngram\": \"the Montmartre\", \"from\": 5307, \"to\": 5321}, {\"ngram\": \"the race cards\", \"from\": 5340, \"to\": 5354}, {\"ngram\": \"the air\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5368}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Favourites like Kopecky, Lorena Wiebes and Demi Vollering (both Netherlands) were all stuck behind when Chloe Dygert (USA) fell heavily, and as a result they were powerless to stop Mavi Garcia from blasting past the break and ahead on the Butte Montmartre.\", \"from\": 5370, \"to\": 5627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5395, \"end\": 5408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorena_Wiebes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lorena Wiebes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorena_Wiebes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lorena_Wiebes\"}, {\"begin\": 5413, \"end\": 5427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Vollering\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Demi Vollering\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Vollering\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Demi_Vollering\"}, {\"begin\": 5435, \"end\": 5446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8580871174604618, \"rank\": 0.16538283736432693, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5475, \"end\": 5487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\", \"score\": 0.9999999166202577, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chloe Dygert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\"}, {\"begin\": 5552, \"end\": 5563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Victoria_Garc\\u00eda\", \"score\": 0.9999999439651235, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mavi Garcia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Victoria_Garc\\u00eda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margarita_Victoria_Garc\\u00eda\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Favourites\", \"from\": 5370, \"to\": 5380}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 5386, \"to\": 5393}, {\"ngram\": \"(USA\", \"from\": 5487, \"to\": 5491}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 5514, \"to\": 5522}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 5582, \"to\": 5591}, {\"ngram\": \"the Butte Montmartre\", \"from\": 5605, \"to\": 5625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Garc\\u00eda's climbing form combined with the crash meant just 10 riders could stay in the first group alongside the Spaniard: Deignan, Henderson and Pfeiffer Georgi (all Great Britain), Vos (Netherlands), Elisa Longo Borghini (Italy), Liane Lippert (Germany), Noemi R\\u00fcegg (Switzerland), Faulkner, Marta Lach (Poland) and Vas.\", \"from\": 5629, \"to\": 5950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5741, \"end\": 5749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9999999999054126, \"rank\": 7.1106162803586e-11, \"text\": \"Spaniard\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 5751, \"end\": 5758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deignan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\"}, {\"begin\": 5760, \"end\": 5769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999995225153, \"rank\": 2.336888229451519e-10, \"text\": \"Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\"}, {\"begin\": 5774, \"end\": 5789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\", \"score\": 0.9999994495557681, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pfeiffer Georgi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pfeiffer_Georgi\", \"d