ource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}, {\"begin\": 5922, \"end\": 5932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_Lach\", \"score\": 0.9999991854077641, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marta Lach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_Lach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marta_Lach\"}, {\"begin\": 5934, \"end\": 5940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999763224952506, \"rank\": 2.3677531106034952e-05, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Garc\\u00eda's climbing form\", \"from\": 5629, \"to\": 5651}, {\"ngram\": \"the crash\", \"from\": 5666, \"to\": 5675}, {\"ngram\": \"just 10 riders\", \"from\": 5682, \"to\": 5696}, {\"ngram\": \"the first group\", \"from\": 5711, \"to\": 5726}, {\"ngram\": \"Vas\", \"from\": 5946, \"to\": 5949}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Crucially though, Kopecky was also quickly able to regain contact, meaning that her theoretically weaker team support was no longer relevant for the Belgian's chances.\", \"from\": 5952, \"to\": 6119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6101, \"end\": 6108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.7906015931642482, \"rank\": 0.26485902575764675, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 5970, \"to\": 5977}, {\"ngram\": \"contact\", \"from\": 6010, \"to\": 6017}, {\"ngram\": \"her theoretically weaker team support\", \"from\": 6032, \"to\": 6069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other top nation, the Netherlands arguably came off worse as a result of the crash, forcing them to burn out Vollering to try and bring their top contender, Wiebes back into play.\", \"from\": 6120, \"to\": 6303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6146, \"end\": 6157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8580871174604618, \"rank\": 0.16538283736432693, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The other top nation\", \"from\": 6120, \"to\": 6140}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 6185, \"to\": 6193}, {\"ngram\": \"the crash\", \"from\": 6197, \"to\": 6206}, {\"ngram\": \"Vollering\", \"from\": 6233, \"to\": 6242}, {\"ngram\": \"their top contender\", \"from\": 6260, \"to\": 6279}, {\"ngram\": \"Wiebes\", \"from\": 6281, \"to\": 6287}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 6298, \"to\": 6302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But their pursuit proved to be a fruitless exercise, and as a result, essentially their race boiled down to seeing what a veteran player like Vos, clearly in great form, could now achieve in the front group of 12.\", \"from\": 6304, \"to\": 6517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their pursuit\", \"from\": 6308, \"to\": 6321}, {\"ngram\": \"a fruitless exercise\", \"from\": 6335, \"to\": 6355}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 6364, \"to\": 6372}, {\"ngram\": \"their race\", \"from\": 6386, \"to\": 6396}, {\"ngram\": \"a veteran player\", \"from\": 6424, \"to\": 6440}, {\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 6446, \"to\": 6449}, {\"ngram\": \"great form\", \"from\": 6462, \"to\": 6472}, {\"ngram\": \"the front group\", \"from\": 6495, \"to\": 6510}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given Britain's superior numbers in that front group, logically Deignan worked hard to keep them clear, helping the dozen maintain a gap of 40 seconds with 38 kilometres to go.\", \"from\": 6519, \"to\": 6695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6525, \"end\": 6532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.8842608093332707, \"rank\": 0.13088773230327946, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 6583, \"end\": 6590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deignan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that front group\", \"from\": 6555, \"to\": 6571}, {\"ngram\": \"the dozen\", \"from\": 6631, \"to\": 6640}, {\"ngram\": \"a gap\", \"from\": 6650, \"to\": 6655}, {\"ngram\": \"40 seconds\", \"from\": 6659, \"to\": 6669}, {\"ngram\": \"38 kilometres\", \"from\": 6675, \"to\": 6688}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a perilously small advantage, though, and come the second of three ascents of the Butte Montmartre, though, the collaboration between the 12 became seriously limited.\", \"from\": 6696, \"to\": 6869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6791, \"end\": 6801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7408908238508796e-16, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a perilously small advantage\", \"from\": 6703, \"to\": 6731}, {\"ngram\": \"three ascents\", \"from\": 6764, \"to\": 6777}, {\"ngram\": \"the collaboration\", \"from\": 6811, \"to\": 6828}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matters only worsened when Henderson tried to take advantage of Great Britain's theoretical strength to launch an attack, only for Garcia to reel her in a few seconds, while Georgi's cunning move over the top of the Montmartre was almost equally rapidly chased down by Kopecky in person.\", \"from\": 6871, \"to\": 7158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6898, \"end\": 6907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999995225153, \"rank\": 2.336888229451519e-10, \"text\": \"Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\"}, {\"begin\": 6935, \"end\": 6948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9949418724559201, \"rank\": 0.005083810857900807, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 7002, \"end\": 7008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\", \"score\": 0.9997668862247263, \"rank\": 0.00023316812982057732, \"text\": \"Garcia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerry_Garcia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Matters\", \"from\": 6871, \"to\": 6878}, {\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 6922, \"to\": 6931}, {\"ngram\": \"an attack\", \"from\": 6982, \"to\": 6991}, {\"ngram\": \"a few seconds\", \"from\": 7024, \"to\": 7037}, {\"ngram\": \"while Georgi's cunning move\", \"from\": 7039, \"to\": 7066}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 7072, \"to\": 7079}, {\"ngram\": \"the Montmartre\", \"from\": 7083, \"to\": 7097}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 7140, \"to\": 7147}, {\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 7151, \"to\": 7157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A sudden, almost inexplicable moment of calm in the front group did allow a suffering Henderson and Deignan to regain contact and drive straight through on the attack.\", \"from\": 7160, \"to\": 7327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7246, \"end\": 7255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999995225153, \"rank\": 2.336888229451519e-10, \"text\": \"Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\"}, {\"begin\": 7260, \"end\": 7267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deignan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A sudden, almost inexplicable moment\", \"from\": 7160, \"to\": 7196}, {\"ngram\": \"calm\", \"from\": 7200, \"to\": 7204}, {\"ngram\": \"the front group\", \"from\": 7208, \"to\": 7223}, {\"ngram\": \"contact\", \"from\": 7278, \"to\": 7285}, {\"ngram\": \"the attack\", \"from\": 7316, \"to\": 7326}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Deignan's subsequent solo offensive only proved instrumental for her rivals' success, not her own.\", \"from\": 7328, \"to\": 7435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7337, \"end\": 7344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deignan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her rivals' success\", \"from\": 7402, \"to\": 7421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vos and multiple Hungarian National Champion Blanka Vas quickly rejoined the Briton and promptly dropped her, forming a break of two with 20 kilometres to go that looked likely to go all the way to the finish.\", \"from\": 7437, \"to\": 7646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7454, \"end\": 7463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999999992696758, \"rank\": 7.296194752378997e-10, \"text\": \"Hungarian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}, {\"begin\": 7482, \"end\": 7492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\", \"score\": 0.9999999946312528, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Blanka Vas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blanka_Vas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 7437, \"to\": 7440}, {\"ngram\": \"the Briton\", \"from\": 7510, \"to\": 7520}, {\"ngram\": \"a break\", \"from\": 7555, \"to\": 7562}, {\"ngram\": \"two with 20 kilometres\", \"from\": 7566, \"to\": 7588}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 7635, \"to\": 7645}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind Kopecky was looking less and less effective and Deignan and Henderson, the other clear powerhouse in the break, had obviously burned all their matches.\", \"from\": 7648, \"to\": 7806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7703, \"end\": 7710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Deignan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Herbert_Girton_Deignan\"}, {\"begin\": 7715, \"end\": 7724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9999999995225153, \"rank\": 2.336888229451519e-10, \"text\": \"Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gerald_Henderson_Jr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 7655, \"to\": 7662}, {\"ngram\": \"the other clear powerhouse\", \"from\": 7726, \"to\": 7752}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 7756, \"to\": 7765}, {\"ngram\": \"all their matches\", \"from\": 7788, \"to\": 7805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vos and Vas, on the other hand, were both working superbly well together, taking turns smoothly and stretching their gap to 40 seconds with 15 kilometres to go.\", \"from\": 7807, \"to\": 7967, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 7807, \"to\": 7810}, {\"ngram\": \"Vas\", \"from\": 7815, \"to\": 7818}, {\"ngram\": \"the other hand\", \"from\": 7823, \"to\": 7837}, {\"ngram\": \"turns\", \"from\": 7888, \"to\": 7893}, {\"ngram\": \"their gap\", \"from\": 7918, \"to\": 7927}, {\"ngram\": \"40 seconds\", \"from\": 7931, \"to\": 7941}, {\"ngram\": \"15 kilometres\", \"from\": 7947, \"to\": 7960}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet just when it seemed that they had the gold and silver medals in their clutches, though, in the umpteenth twist in the race, a chase group of Kopecky, Noemi R\\u00fcegg (Switzerland), Giorgi, Faulkner and Garc\\u00eda began working harder together, somehow keeping the remnants of the break of 12 just about in contention.\", \"from\": 7969, \"to\": 8282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8123, \"end\": 8134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noemi_R\\u00fcegg\", \"score\": 0.9999999726569516, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noemi R\\u00fcegg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noemi_R\\u00fcegg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noemi_R\\u00fcegg\"}, {\"begin\": 8136, \"end\": 8147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.986566238456392, \"rank\": 0.01361638857815109, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 8150, \"end\": 8156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_III_of_Georgia\", \"score\": 0.9999988228116871, \"rank\": 6.486488954512381e-07, \"text\": \"Giorgi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_III_of_Georgia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_III_of_Georgia\"}, {\"begin\": 8158, \"end\": 8166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6526612414421133e-25, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gold and silver medals\", \"from\": 8007, \"to\": 8033}, {\"ngram\": \"their clutches\", \"from\": 8037, \"to\": 8051}, {\"ngram\": \"the umpteenth twist\", \"from\": 8064, \"to\": 8083}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 8087, \"to\": 8095}, {\"ngram\": \"a chase group\", \"from\": 8097, \"to\": 8110}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 8114, \"to\": 8121}, {\"ngram\": \"Garc\\u00eda\", \"from\": 8171, \"to\": 8177}, {\"ngram\": \"the remnants\", \"from\": 8225, \"to\": 8237}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 8241, \"to\": 8250}, {\"ngram\": \"contention\", \"from\": 8271, \"to\": 8281}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Vas led Vos onto the third and definitive ascent of the Butte Montmartre, they still had some 20 seconds in hand.\", \"from\": 8284, \"to\": 8402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8351, \"end\": 8361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7408908238508796e-16, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Vas\", \"from\": 8289, \"to\": 8292}, {\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 8297, \"to\": 8300}, {\"ngram\": \"the third and definitive ascent\", \"from\": 8306, \"to\": 8337}, {\"ngram\": \"some 20 seconds\", \"from\": 8378, \"to\": 8393}, {\"ngram\": \"hand\", \"from\": 8397, \"to\": 8401}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, nobody had anything to lose by this point and after Faulkner started driving as hard as possible in a last fling of the dice, her ferocious acceleration simultaneously meant not only that Kopecky could cling on behind her back wheel, but also that the leading duo's advantage began to wear perilously thin.\", \"from\": 8403, \"to\": 8718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8464, \"end\": 8472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6526612414421133e-25, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 8412, \"to\": 8418}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 8423, \"to\": 8431}, {\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 8443, \"to\": 8453}, {\"ngram\": \"a last fling\", \"from\": 8512, \"to\": 8524}, {\"ngram\": \"the dice\", \"from\": 8528, \"to\": 8536}, {\"ngram\": \"her ferocious acceleration\", \"from\": 8538, \"to\": 8564}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 8600, \"to\": 8607}, {\"ngram\": \"her back wheel\", \"from\": 8630, \"to\": 8644}, {\"ngram\": \"the leading duo's advantage\", \"from\": 8660, \"to\": 8687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just a handful of seconds separated Vos and Vas from the chasing Belgian and American at the summit of the Montmartre, each group of two working their utmost in a thrilling chase.\", \"from\": 8720, \"to\": 8899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8797, \"end\": 8805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999867177395, \"rank\": 1.3282062788443482e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Just a handful\", \"from\": 8720, \"to\": 8734}, {\"ngram\": \"seconds\", \"from\": 8738, \"to\": 8745}, {\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 8756, \"to\": 8759}, {\"ngram\": \"Vas\", \"from\": 8764, \"to\": 8767}, {\"ngram\": \"the summit\", \"from\": 8809, \"to\": 8819}, {\"ngram\": \"the Montmartre\", \"from\": 8823, \"to\": 8837}, {\"ngram\": \"each group\", \"from\": 8839, \"to\": 8849}, {\"ngram\": \"their utmost\", \"from\": 8865, \"to\": 8877}, {\"ngram\": \"a thrilling chase\", \"from\": 8881, \"to\": 8898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, 3.5 kilometres from the line, the four were reunited, with three medals still at stake and everything to play for.\", \"from\": 8900, \"to\": 9023, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 8929, \"to\": 8937}, {\"ngram\": \"three medals\", \"from\": 8968, \"to\": 8980}, {\"ngram\": \"stake\", \"from\": 8990, \"to\": 8995}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 9000, \"to\": 9010}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Faulkner immediately launched an attack, though, and the moment of hesitation between the three proved fatal.\", \"from\": 9025, \"to\": 9134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9025, \"end\": 9033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6526612414421133e-25, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an attack\", \"from\": 9055, \"to\": 9064}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 9078, \"to\": 9088}, {\"ngram\": \"hesitation\", \"from\": 9092, \"to\": 9102}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an instant as the chasers looked too hard each other, the race was lost.\", \"from\": 9135, \"to\": 9210, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an instant\", \"from\": 9138, \"to\": 9148}, {\"ngram\": \"the chasers\", \"from\": 9152, \"to\": 9163}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 9192, \"to\": 9200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew that Kopecky wanted to catch the front two, so I knew she'd ride with me.\", \"from\": 9212, \"to\": 9293, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 9225, \"to\": 9232}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I also knew that if we caught them, then I had to attack because I could not beat any of them at the line,\\\" Faulkner later explained.\", \"from\": 9294, \"to\": 9427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9402, \"end\": 9410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6526612414421133e-25, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 9391, \"to\": 9399}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew the best place to attack was right after we caught them and everyone was tied.\", \"from\": 9429, \"to\": 9515, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the best place\", \"from\": 9437, \"to\": 9451}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 9497, \"to\": 9505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was my chance.\", \"from\": 9516, \"to\": 9535, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my chance\", \"from\": 9525, \"to\": 9534}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I practised my late attack several times this year, so I felt pretty comfortable with how to do it.\", \"from\": 9537, \"to\": 9637, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my late attack\", \"from\": 9550, \"to\": 9564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I just hoped it worked.\\\"\", \"from\": 9638, \"to\": 9662, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After Faulkner surged away to cross the line for victory, around a minute later Kopecky led out the sprint for the placings, with Vos powering past her right to claim the silver by the narrowest of margins.\", \"from\": 9664, \"to\": 9870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9670, \"end\": 9678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6526612414421133e-25, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the line\", \"from\": 9700, \"to\": 9708}, {\"ngram\": \"victory\", \"from\": 9713, \"to\": 9720}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 9744, \"to\": 9751}, {\"ngram\": \"the sprint\", \"from\": 9760, \"to\": 9770}, {\"ngram\": \"the placings\", \"from\": 9775, \"to\": 9787}, {\"ngram\": \"Vos\", \"from\": 9794, \"to\": 9797}, {\"ngram\": \"her right\", \"from\": 9812, \"to\": 9821}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver\", \"from\": 9831, \"to\": 9841}, {\"ngram\": \"margins\", \"from\": 9862, \"to\": 9869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vas, already fourth in the 2021 Worlds had to settle for finishing outside the medals by the narrowest of margins once again.\", \"from\": 9871, \"to\": 9996, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2021 Worlds\", \"from\": 9894, \"to\": 9909}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 9946, \"to\": 9956}, {\"ngram\": \"margins\", \"from\": 9977, \"to\": 9984}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kopecky was disappointed, but recognised that once Faulkner had gone up the road, there was nothing to be done, saying that they had looked too long at each other, and by that point, Faulkner had the race in the bag.\", \"from\": 9998, \"to\": 10214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10049, \"end\": 10057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6526612414421133e-25, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}, {\"begin\": 10181, \"end\": 10189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6526612414421133e-25, \"text\": \"Faulkner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 9998, \"to\": 10005}, {\"ngram\": \"the road\", \"from\": 10070, \"to\": 10078}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 10090, \"to\": 10097}, {\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 10169, \"to\": 10179}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 10194, \"to\": 10202}, {\"ngram\": \"the bag\", \"from\": 10206, \"to\": 10213}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"On paper, Marianne is the fastest and when you start to think of course\\u2026.\", \"from\": 10216, \"to\": 10290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10227, \"end\": 10235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Dashwood\", \"score\": 0.8862290700073309, \"rank\": 0.12837643657091116, \"text\": \"Marianne\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Dashwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marianne_Dashwood\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"paper\", \"from\": 10220, \"to\": 10225}, {\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 10282, \"to\": 10288}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once Kristen had gone, we knew we would not catch her and then it was a fight for the medals,\\\" said Kopecky.\", \"from\": 10291, \"to\": 10399, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kristen\", \"from\": 10296, \"to\": 10303}, {\"ngram\": \"a fight\", \"from\": 10361, \"to\": 10368}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 10373, \"to\": 10383}, {\"ngram\": \"Kopecky\", \"from\": 10391, \"to\": 10398}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Faulkner meanwhile could savour a remarkable but utterly well-deserved triumph, even if she did not raise her arms in the air when she crossed the line as if unable to fully take in what she had just achieved.\", \"from\": 10401, \"to\": 10610, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10401, \"end\": 10409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Faulkner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.65266